# Project Starter Pack — Cursor rule

## Which workspace is this?

**If the workspace is `Project-Starter-Pack` (this factory repo):**

- Read [README.md](README.md) first, then [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and [WORKFLOW.md](WORKFLOW.md).
- **Do not** improvise folder layout for new apps; only use [template/](template/) and [scripts/bootstrap_new_project.py](scripts/bootstrap_new_project.py).
- When the **user** asks for a **new** project, ask **BROWSER** or **DESKTOP** (unless they already chose), run bootstrap with `--kind`, then continue in the **new sibling folder** (name starts with **`psp-`**) beside the starter pack’s parent, not here.
- **Beat A / Beat B:** use the premium user templates in [docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md](docs/HANDOFF_MESSAGES.md) (tables, copy-friendly code blocks, GitHub **YES** / **NO** in Beat A only). **Beat B** after GitHub or NO — [docs/GITHUB_SETUP_WALKTHROUGH.md](docs/GITHUB_SETUP_WALKTHROUGH.md) Phase 5. Keep this factory repo free of any one user’s paths, usernames, or tokens.

**If the workspace is a child project** created from this pack:

- Follow **that** repo’s [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) and its `.cursor/rules`. Do not treat the child as the starter pack.

The user must not be asked to design filesystem layout or default backups. See [FOR_USER.md](FOR_USER.md).
